1. A user-friendly program should print an introduction that tells the user what the program does. Modify the convert.py program to print an introduction.
--------
# File: 1.2-deliverables-question-1
# Created 12.11.18 by Ksenia Z
# A celsius to fahrenheit converter.

def main():
    # Program Description
    print("This program converts a Celcius temperature")
    print("value into it's Fahrenheit equivalent")
    print("")
    # User temp value input
    celsius = eval(input("What is the Celsius temperature? "))
    # Conversion equation
    fahrenheit = 9 / 5 * celsius + 32
    # Conclusion
    print("The temperature is", fahrenheit, "degrees Fahrenheit.")

main ()
